    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: U0151"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "U0151",
      "text": "DTC U0151: F-CAN communication error (PGM-FI ECU-SRS unit communication failure)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2149_3.0_jpn_11231355_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The control unit-to-control unit communication (F-CAN) for powertrain/chassis systems uses two communication lines (F-CAN_H and F-CAN_L) to send and receive multiple signals simultaneously between multiple control units. If signals from the SRS unit sent using F-CAN_H and F-CAN_L are not received for a predetermined period of time, the PGM-FI ECU determines a failure and stores the DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection execution conditions"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection frequency"
          },
          {
            "text": "24-hour (e.g. observation, operation (of a machine), care (of patient))"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "（Detection order (of the DTC in question)"
          },
          {
            "text": "nashi (Pyrus pyrifolia, esp. var. culta)"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection time"
          },
          {
            "text": "More than 1.5 seconds"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection method type"
          },
          {
            "text": "1D/C (single detection method), PGM-FI warning light: off"
          }
        ],
        [
